         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Treasury Melbourne ¶ 17 January 1865 ¶ Circular No 425. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I am directed by the Honble the Treasurer to request that heads of Departments in your Division of the service may be instructed tha...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.01.17a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Edward Symonds</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Director’s letterbooks, MVS 2/1 2, f. 410, Melbourne Museum.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Treasury Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17 January 1865</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Circular No 425.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am directed by the Honble the Treasurer to request that heads of Departments in your Division of the service may be instructed that whenever it is necessary to inflict a fine on Contractors or other persons to whom monies are payable by the Government an [Indent] Voucher is to be prepared &amp; forwarded under Cover of a special letter of advice to this office with the first account which may become due to the person fined in order that the necessary stoppage may be made.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(signed) E. S. Symonds</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Honble</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Chief Secretary<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Frederick McCoy had the circular transcribed into his outward letterbook and then added a note: ‘noted &amp; forwarded to Director of Botanic garden. | 8/2/65. F. McC.’</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
